<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1506,1926]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,324,1506,1531]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" reason="1">Redescription.</emphasis>
Forewings 2.1 times longer than wide, length: female about 
<quantity box="[1006,1095,1506,1530]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
. Stramineous, forewings powdered, faintly infuscated along parts of M, R and Sc, slightly stronger around first subcostal sector; veins stramineous to light orange in basal 1/3rd, orange-red in posterior 2/3rd. Hindwings colourless, veins light red.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1506,1926]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
